cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.MA

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless power transfer and data transmission in a multiuser mobile sensing system, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The optimization problem formulated in the paper involves controlling wireless power allocation and sensing-data sizes, which are related to systems and control.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses lossless and lossy compression, which are fundamental concepts in information theory.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper involves data sensing, compression, and transmission, which are related to multimedia applications.
5. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper considers multiple mobile sensors and an access point, which can be viewed as a multi-agent system.
